<br>
<br>
First, look at the map, print it out.  Keep it handy.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/m2/hateplane1.jpg">www.eqmaps.com/m2/hateplane1.jpg</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
When you port up, make sure the entire group is invis.  You can also invis your wizzie buy casting on him, then yourself right as he begins the port.  You will zone into POH at the are marked 1, in the South East corner of the zone.  Quickly move out, making two rights, to the wall, and move up halfway, so you dont aggro the ceiling mobs, but are away from the street, as well.<br>
<br>
At this point, you can choose either invis, or IVU (undead).  Some mobs will see each one, but MOST wont see IVU, the choice is up to you.<br>
<br>
You contine to move right along the wall (south) maintaining yourself halfway up, neither to high or too low.  You quickly turn the corner and are now heading West, twords the South West Corner (SWC).  Keep your eyes on the street below you, sevral roamers will path right to the wall, and some will even path 1/4 up the wall.  Do not attempt to run past if they con anything but indiffrent.  if you have some patience and luck, you will be able to wait them out, and run past when they path away.  If you get aggro, STAND AND DIE, do not train, if you can FD, do it, and log out and come back.  Let me repeat<br>
<br>
STAND AND DIE.<br>
<br>
Only exceptions are ppl who can FD, or root/camp out.  If you train the camp at SWC you will cost us hours on CR, and money for more hate stones.<br>
<br>
Once you arrive to the true South West Corner, make sure you do not pass building S at ground level, there are sevral traps which spawn Tiney Imps.  Once past S, wait patiently on the wall (still halfway up) between buildings S and R.  Rogues will procede to drag bodies of the fallen (there will be a LOT, this isnt easy, and requires a bit of luck).  Clerics will begin rezing, untill everyone is at the SWC camp.<br>
<br>
At this point the Pull group takes over, everyone should have primary and secondary assist keys set up.  Pull group sets the pace, everyone else just sits at camp and kills what is brought.<br>
<br>
